6.6.19  4:02 am   do you enjoy making music because it's an inherently enjoyable experience (like taking a breath of fresh air),

     better than that

      or because it's affirming to spend time doing something you're good at,

     that can be nice too, but that also means i can have very high standards and hate myself sometimes temporarily

      or maybe because the fact that you're good means that the music you're creating is enjoyable

     i am convinced that that can always ultimately be the end result, despite the occasional oceans of hesitation and confusion which may happen in the middle

      in the same way that you enjoy listening to your favorite music made by other people?

     that would be cool, maybe even better in some ways, to make up for ways it may be not as good

      That is, is the satisfying part the action of creating, the esteem (self or otherwise), or the product? Or some combination of the three?

     combination of that and more i think
